author: Richard Barley
title: U.S. Treasurys Again Call the Global Bond-Market Tune
text:
The trans-Atlantic pressure is rising—at least in the bond market.
Last year, a relentless rally in German bond yields—fueled in part by an ever-growing expectation of quantitative easing from the European Central Bank—helped drag down U.S. Treasury yields. That confounded many who expected them to rise.
